properties.desc: You find yourself at the base of a massive tower, the likes of which looks to stretch to the sun.
You see what once was an alchemists lab. It's just rubble now.
You find a suspiciously pristine room, housing a local healer trainer.
The local mage trainer lives in a building in tatters. There are books strewn about.
The local thief trainer is stuck in a building that couldn't hide the darkest shadow.
What once was a thriving center is filled to the brim with broken, discarded remnants of the life that once was here.
The local tanner doesn't even have a fur to stand on.
You see the local smith huddled in a corner, no hearth to warm the room.
The local fighter trainer seems unfazed by the broken structures surrounding him.
As you climb the stairs, the acrid stench of blood fills your nostrils.
You enter a room and see weapons littering the walls. This appears to have been weapon storage for the entire tower, once upon a time.
You enter the room and see armor dolls along the walls. This must have housed all of the armor for the tower.
As you enter the room, you step through piles of broken weapons. This must have been a sparring chamber, but time has not been kind to it.
You find a small trace of civilization in the tower. The guards ready their weapons at your approach, uneasy towards a newcomer.
The bright pyres illuminate the room and it's centrally located dragon statue. Perhaps the tower is inhabited by strange worshippers?
A grand fountain fills the view of the room. It seems well-kept for its presumed age.
You see bags of food, some spoiled, some not. Barrels, books, and buckets litter the floor. It looks like a storage room.
You see an eccentric, strange creature as you enter the door.
You see a singular statue in this room. Seems the tower appreciated art in their own way.
As you enter, the unbearable stench of rotten eggs overwhelms you. A single man stands out among the guards.
You find yourself on a strange floating island. You wonder briefly how it stays up before letting the thought pass.
